07:53.040 --> 07:54.393
- FINE.

07:54.440 --> 07:58.103
I GUESS I'LL JUST FIND
SCO'I'I' SEAVER BY MYSELF, SOLO.

07:58.140 --> 07:59.573
- YOU DON'T KNOW HOW TO DO IT
SOLO, SHAWN.

07:59.610 --> 08:00.599
THAT'S MY DEPARTMENT.

08:00.640 --> 08:01.834
- SOUNDS LIKE A CHALLENGE.

08:01.880 --> 08:02.847
- IT'S NOT A CHALLENGE.

08:02.880 --> 08:04.006
- CHALLENGE ACCEPTED.

08:04.050 --> 08:05.472
- WILL YOU GET OUT OF HERE?

08:08.550 --> 08:09.517
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

08:09.550 --> 08:10.915
- I HAVE A MEETING
WITH...SOMEONE.

08:10.950 --> 08:12.087
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

08:12.120 --> 08:13.553
- I SOLVED JULIET'S CASE.
- YOU DID NOT.

08:13.590 --> 08:14.784
- YES, I DID.

08:14.820 --> 08:15.957
- ALL RIGHT, LET ME BE THE ONE
TO BREAK IT TO HER.

08:15.990 --> 08:16.957
- NOPE, ABSOLUTELY NOT.

08:16.990 --> 08:17.979
- SHE HIRED ME, SHAWN.

08:18.030 --> 08:19.179
- GUS, IT WAS A TRICKY FIND.

08:19.230 --> 08:20.857
I WANT ALL THE GLORY
FOR SOLVING JULES' CASE.

08:20.900 --> 08:24.324
BESIDES, I AM THE ONE
THAT DOES THIS.

08:24.370 --> 08:25.962
WOULDN'T IT BE WEIRD
