- NO.

08:31.910 --> 08:33.400
- HUH.
WELL, AT LEAST WE HAVE THAT.

08:33.440 --> 08:34.702
- SHAWN.
- JULES!

08:34.740 --> 08:37.470
GUS LET ME IN ON YOUR
LI'I'I'LE MISSING PERSONS CASE.

08:37.510 --> 08:38.545
- YOU WHAT?

08:38.580 --> 08:39.842
- YOUR RANDOM
MISSING PERSONS CASE,

08:39.880 --> 08:41.370
THE PERSON
YOU'VE NEVER MET BEFORE.

08:41.420 --> 08:42.842
- YEAH, I'VE GOT
SOME GOOD NEWS/ BAD NEWS

08:42.890 --> 08:44.585
ON THIS SCOTI' SEAVER FELLOW.

08:44.620 --> 08:46.781
BAD NEWS IS HE'S DEAD.
- WHAT?

08:46.820 --> 08:49.288
- DOORNAIL. THAT'S WHY YOU HAD
SUCH A HARD TIME FINDING HIM.

08:49.320 --> 08:51.481
- SHAWN?
- WHAT?

08:51.530 --> 08:53.395
- OH, MY GOD.

08:57.500 --> 08:59.092
- JULES?

08:59.130 --> 09:01.166
MAN, SHE REALLY TAKES
THESE CASES SERIOUSLY.

09:01.200 --> 09:03.407
- IT WAS HER BOYFRIEND, SHAWN.
HER COLLEGE BOYFRIEND.

09:03.440 --> 09:05.431
- WHAT? YOU SAID SHE NEVER
EVEN MET THIS GUY.

09:05.470 --> 09:06.437
- I LIED.
- WHY?

09:06.470 --> 09:07.732
- WHAT DIFFERENCE
DOES IT MAKE?

09:07.780 --> 09:09.577
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY BE THE
GOOD NEWS COMING AFI'ER THAT?

09:12.880 --> 09:14.848
- I WAS GONNA SAY THE GOOD NEWS
